newOptionType(address,uint96,address,uin.details: optionId can be precomputed using  uint160 optionKey = uint160(      bytes20(          keccak256(              abi.encode(                  underlyingAsset,                  underlyingAmount,                  exerciseAsset,                  exerciseAmount,                  exerciseTimestamp,                  expiryTimestamp,                  uint160(0),                  uint96(0)              )          )      )  );  optionId = uint256(optionKey) << OPTION_ID_PADDING; and then tokenType(optionId) == TokenType.Option if the option already exists.

params.exerciseAmount: The amount of exerciseAsset, in wei, required to exercise each option contract.
params.exerciseAsset: The contract address of the ERC20 exercise asset.
params.exerciseTimestamp: The timestamp after which this option can be exercised.
params.expiryTimestamp: The timestamp before which this option can be exercised.
params.underlyingAmount: The amount of underlyingAsset, in wei, collateralizing each option contract.
params.underlyingAsset: The contract address of the ERC20 underlying asset.

acceptFeeTo().notice: Accepts the new feeTo address and completes the update. See also setFeeTo(address newFeeTo).

exercise(uint256,uint112).notice: Exercises specified amount of optionId, transferring in the exercise asset, and transferring out the underlying asset if requirements are met. Can be called from exercise timestamp (inclusive), until option expiry timestamp (exclusive).

feeBalance(address).notice: Gets the balance of protocol fees for a given token which have not been swept yet.

feeBps().notice: Gets the protocol fee, expressed in basis points.

feeTo().notice: Returns the address to which protocol fees are swept.

feesEnabled().notice: Checks if protocol fees are enabled.

newOptionType(address,uint96,address,uin.notice: Creates a new option contract type if it doesn't already exist.

position(uint256).notice: Gets information about the ERC20 token positions of an option or claim.

redeem(uint256).notice: Redeems a claim NFT, transfers the underlying/exercise tokens to the caller. Can be called after option expiry timestamp (inclusive).

setFeeTo(address).notice: Nominates a new address to which fees should be swept, requiring the new feeTo address to accept before the update is complete. See also acceptFeeTo().

setTokenURIGenerator(address).notice: Updates the contract address for generating token URIs for tokens.

sweepFees(address[]).notice: Sweeps fees to the feeTo address if there is more than 1 wei for feeBalance for a given token.

tokenType(uint256).notice: Gets the TokenType for a given tokenId.

uri(uint256).notice: Returns the URI for a given tokenId.

write(uint256,uint112).notice: Writes a specified amount of the specified option, returning claim NFT id.

@notice Performs fair exercise assignment via the pseudorandom selection of an
 unexercised or partially exercised bucket. If the exercise amount overflows into
 another bucket, the buckets are iterated from oldest to newest. The pseudorandom
 index seed is updated accordingly on the option type.
